    "Ensuring that DL models are adaptable to both perspectives will assist in their adoption within the field, whilst maintaining continuity with previous work (2012 (, Rayfield 2007;; Bakker et al. 2020).",
    "In addition to addressing these professional challenges, DL approaches can also benefit amateur paleontologists and the general public by enabling approximate identification of fossils at broader taxonomic levels.",
    "This capability can help manage the influx of fossil images submitted by the public, reducing the workload on professional paleontologists and allowing them to focus on more specialised analyses.",
    "Ultimately, the integration of DL in paleontological tasks such as fossil classification and segmentation can pave the way for more nuanced and comprehensive studies in the field, offering insights into the subtle differences that define species differentiation and evolutionary trajectories.",
    "In recent years, there has been a notable increase in research on DL applications in fossil image analysis, with classification emerging as the dominant focus."
